  "displayName": "Kora Framework — Java/Kotlin Backend Developer",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "highlights": [
    "Fastest JVM framework: 50–100ms startup time",
    "6x less memory than Spring Boot (~50MB idle)",
    "Compile-time DI: zero reflection, zero proxies, zero runtime magic",
    "AI-friendly: readable generated source code",
    "Virtual threads for massive concurrency (Java 21+)",
    "15 production-ready sub-skills: HTTP, Database, Kafka, gRPC, S3, OpenAPI, Telemetry"
  ],
  "description": "Build production-grade Java/Kotlin microservices with Kora Framework — the fastest JVM backend framework. Compile-time dependency injection, no reflection or bytecode generation, annotation-processor driven (Java) or KSP driven (Kotlin). Perfect for AI agents and cloud-native microservices. Includes 15 specialized sub-skills: HTTP server/client, Kafka, JDBC/Cassandra, gRPC, S3, OpenAPI codegen, caching (Caffeine/Redis), resilience (CircuitBreaker/Retry), scheduling, validation, MapStruct, and full observability (OpenTelemetry + Micrometer).",
